OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780966989
OL,3,CMay heatwave boosts spending on
OL,4,Cbarbecue food, sandals and sunglasses
OL,6,FMay's heatwave drove a surge in
OL,7,Fspending on products ranging from
OL,8,Fbarbecue food to sandals and
OL,9,Fsunglasses in a boost to retailers,
OL,10,Ffigures show.
OL,12,FTotal UK retail sales increased by
OL,13,F3.7% year on year in May, well above
OL,14,Fthe 12-month average of 2%, according
OL,15,Fto data from the British Retail
OL,16,FConsortium (BRC) and KPMG.
OL,18,FFood sales were up 3.9% on last May as
OL,19,Fhouseholds made the most of the bank
OL,20,Fholiday weather by lighting barbecues.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,304,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780966989
OL,3,CMay heatwave boosts spending on
OL,4,Cbarbecue food, sandals and sunglasses
OL,6,FThe hot temperatures drove a 3.5% year-
OL,7,Fon-year increase in non-food sales ` a
OL,8,Fjump from the 12-month average growth
OL,9,Fof 0.7% ` as shoppers scrambled to buy
OL,10,Fsummer essentials such as sandals and
OL,11,Fsunglasses, fans, cooler bedding and
OL,12,Foutdoor toys.
OL,14,FOnline sales were particularly
OL,15,Fhealthy, up by 10.6% year on year, as
OL,16,Fmany opted to shop from home to avoid
OL,17,Fthe heat.
OL,19,FBRC chief executive Helen Dickinson
OL,20,Fsaid: "May's heatwave drove a surge in
OL,21,Foutdoor and summer goods.
OL,26,@|D@GOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/8
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
