CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780966989
OL,3,CMay heatwave boosts spending on
OL,4,Cbarbecue food, sandals and sunglasses
OL,6,F"Clothing and footwear returned to
OL,7,Fgrowth as shoppers snapped up summer
OL,8,Fessentials like sandals and sunglasses.
OL,10,F"As temperatures rose, many opted to
OL,11,Fshop online to avoid the heat,
OL,12,Fboosting online sales."
OL,14,FLinda Ellett, UK head of consumer,
OL,15,Fretail and leisure at KPMG, said: "The
OL,16,Flate spring heatwave brought record
OL,17,Ftemperatures in May and also heated up
OL,18,Fretail sales growth.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUtD@WO]wD@cOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/8
