OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780966989
OL,3,CMay heatwave boosts spending on
OL,4,Cbarbecue food, sandals and sunglasses
OL,6,F"Clothing and footwear sales grew `
OL,7,Fsome for the first time since the
OL,8,FJanuary sales.
OL,10,F"Hot days and nights increased fans
OL,11,Fand air con unit buying, while food
OL,12,Fand drink sales were up, as were
OL,13,Fgarden-related purchases.
OL,15,F"As we move into the summer season,
OL,16,Fretailers and hospitality businesses
OL,17,Fwill be hoping the good weather
OL,18,Fcontinues and that the World Cup
OL,19,Fboosts related spending.
OL,26,@nD@AOUrD@AOUwD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/8
