CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780966989
OL,3,CMay heatwave boosts spending on
OL,4,Cbarbecue food, sandals and sunglasses
OL,6,FConcerns about the impact of the
OL,7,FMiddle East on costs remain high but
OL,8,Feased slightly month on month, with
OL,9,F83% of consumers currently concerned
OL,10,Fabout rising energy bills, down from
OL,11,F85%, and 82% now worried about food
OL,12,Fprices, down from 84%.
OL,14,FTravel spending fell 5.8%, marking its
OL,15,Fthird consecutive month of decline,
OL,16,Fwith holidaymakers still taking a wait-
OL,17,Fand-see approach to their summer plans
OL,18,Famid ongoing uncertainty.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/8
