OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F303A1780966989
OL,3,CMay heatwave boosts spending on
OL,4,Cbarbecue food, sandals and sunglasses
OL,6,FKaren Johnson, head of retail at
OL,7,FBarclays, said: "The warmer weather
OL,8,Fand first May bank holiday gave
OL,9,Fconsumers more reasons to spend in
OL,10,FMay, particularly on seasonal
OL,11,Fessentials, UK breaks and affordable
OL,12,Fways to enjoy time with family and
OL,13,Ffriends.
OL,15,F"Shoppers are still being careful,
OL,16,Fwith many continuing to build savings
OL,17,Fand managing subscriptions more
OL,18,Fclosely, but they are also finding
OL,19,Froom in their budgets for the things
OL,20,Fthat feel good value, convenient or
OL,21,Fworth prioritising."
